<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,312,1079,1105]" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
. The association of males and females, which come from different localities, is based on their extremely similar external appearance. Additional support for this putative association is derived also from similarity in the female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[582,689,1157,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravida">
<emphasis box="[582,597,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[612,689,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">ravida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which bear much resemblance to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1212,1358,1157,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlinella">
<emphasis box="[1212,1227,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1242,1358,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">carlinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as do those of males of the two species.
</paragraph>
